title: 12 Chess Books (gnv64)
description:
Here is one more collection of my chess books for the chesslovers! (10 PDF + 2 ePUB):

01. Coffeehouse Chess Tactics by John Healy (4.7 mb)
02. Counterplay - An Anthropologist at the Chessboard by Robert R Desjarlais (5.7 mb)
03. How to Become a Deadly Chess Tactician by David LeMoir (7.71 mb)
04. Isolani Strategy - Strenghts and Weaknesses of the Isolated Quenn's Pawn by Belyavsky, Mikhalchishin, Stetsko (17.4 mb)
05. Move First, Think Later - Sense and Nonsense in Improving Your Chess by Willy Hendriks (6.24 mb)
06. Playing 1.d4 The Queen's Gambit (Grandmaster Guide) by Lars Schandorff (6.71 mb)
07. Positional Chess Sacrifices by Mihai Suba (8.61 mb)
08. Profession Chessplayer - Grandmaster at Work by Vladimir Tukmakov (9.71 mb)
09. Quickest Chess Victories of All Time by Graham Burgess (11.8 mb)
10. The King - Chess Pieces by J H Donner (10.7 mb)
11. Tune Your Chess Tactics Antenna Know When (and where!) to Look for Winning Combinations by Emmanuel Neiman (12.1 mb)
12. United States Chess Federation's Official Rules of Chess (6th Ed) by Tim Just (4.04 mb)
